Re: Does this make sense?
by Hyperworm » Thu 06.16.2011 5:16 pm Cyborg Ninja wrote:By the way, I'm impressed you know that the period goes before the closing quotation mark in English. Not even many native English speakers know that.You should read this article.I've seen it done both ways in Japanese, too, and personally got the impression that "outside the quotes" is more common, but I could be wrong. fun translation snippets | need something translated?BTC@1KMZXgoWiDshQis5Z7feCx8jaiP4QAB2ks
