Re: Does this make sense?
by blutorange » Thu 06.16.2011 5:29 pm Let me quote my opinion:"When quoting a sentence, everything goes between the quotation marks, such as the openers Japanese sentence."However, when quoting some instance within a sentence, then the hierarchy becomes sentence first, quote last. So, by that I mean "this". What's quoted goes between those marks.
