Re: Does this make sense?
by furrykef » Mon 06.20.2011 4:59 am My usual convention is "logical" quotation for straight quote marks and the conventional American quotation for curly quote marks. In other words, it depends on the typesetting.People who insist that one style or the other is "correct" and the other isn't, though, need to learn that style != correctness. Getting back on topic, Blutorange's sentence is exactly what I would have said too.
